NAME
    tee - read from stdin and write to stdout and files

SYNOPSIS
    tee [-a] <file>...

DESCRIPTION
    Copies stdin to stdout and also writes to the specified files.
    Useful for capturing pipeline output while still passing it through.

OPTIONS
    -a, --append
            Append to files instead of overwriting

EXAMPLES
    find . | tee /tmp/files.txt
        Save file list while displaying it

    find . | tee /tmp/files.txt | wc -l
        Save and count files

    cat data | tee -a /tmp/log.txt
        Append to log file

    cat file | tee /tmp/a.txt /tmp/b.txt
        Write to multiple files

SEE ALSO
    cat, echo
